Ros Agro Plc (AGRO) , a Russian agricultural
producer listed in  London , said meat and fodder output dropped
in April.  Meat production declined 18 percent from a year earlier to
5,200 metric tons, Ros Agro, also known as Rusagro, said today
in an e-mailed statement, citing management accounts. Fodder for
sale also fell 18 percent to 5,800 tons, it said.  Margarine output slumped 28 percent to about 1,900 tons,
while mayonnaise production increased 5 percent to 4,900 tons,
the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
